# Dual UAV-assisted ISAC: A DRL-based framework

Dual UAV-assisted ISAC (Integrated Sensing and Communication) with two cooperative UAVs trained via Deep RL. This repo focuses on Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) with TD3 baseline, and a MAPPO plan (stub) for future multi-agent centralized-critic.

- First-class: SAC training pipeline and evaluation
- Baselines: TD3, simple heuristics (circle/greedy)
- Metrics: communication utility, sensing utility, energy, safety, secrecy proxy
- Roadmap: security-aware features (artificial noise, jammer mode), MAPPO, richer channels

## Quickstart

```bash
# Install (Python 3.11)
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install tensorboard  # Optional but recommended for training logs

# Option 1: Quick demo (short training + evaluation + plots)
python -m src.scripts.demo

# Option 2: Full training pipeline
# Train SAC
python -m src.training.train_sac --total_timesteps 300000 --alpha 0.5 --n_users 8 --n_targets 1 --save_dir runs/sac_a05_u8_t1

# Evaluate trained model
python -m src.eval.eval_rollout --model_path runs/sac_a05_u8_t1/model.zip --alpha 0.5 --n_episodes 20

# Run baselines for comparison
python -m src.eval.eval_rollout --baseline circle --alpha 0.5 --n_episodes 20 --out runs/baselines/circle
python -m src.eval.eval_rollout --baseline greedy_comms --alpha 0.5 --n_episodes 20 --out runs/baselines/greedy_comms

# Plot results from one or many runs
python -m src.eval.plots --inputs runs/*/results.jsonl --out reports/figures

# View training curves (optional)
tensorboard --logdir runs
```

## Environment (MDP)
- 2 UAVs in a 2D 2000×2000 m area; altitude z ∈ [80, 180] m; dt = 1 s; vmax = 25 m/s
- Users (N=6–10) fixed in (x,y); Targets (T=1–2) with (x,y), confidence state
- Optional eavesdropper sector (angle ±spread)

### Action (per UAV, Box[-1,1], 5 dims)
[Δheading, speed_frac, Δz_norm, time_split_sense, power_split_AN]
- Internally mapped to physical units; fractions are clamped to [0,1]

### Observation (normalized ~[-1,1])
- UAVs: x, y, z, heading, battery (2×5)
- Users: positions (N×2), deficits (N)
- Targets: positions (T×2), confidence (T)
- Time-left scalar
- Optional coarse no-fly 10×10 mask (flattened)

### Reward (clamped to [-1,1])

r = α·CommsUtility + (1-α)·SensingUtility − λ·EnergyUse − μ·SafetyViolations − η·LeakageProxy

- CommsUtility: users assigned to nearest UAV; SNR ≈ K_c / d_3D^2; sum log2(1+SNR), scaled by (1-avg time_split_sense)·(1-avg power_split_AN)
- SensingUtility: higher when close to targets and with wider UAV baseline around target, scaled by avg time_split_sense
- EnergyUse: movement (speed^2), altitude change cost, small tx cost
- SafetyViolations: min UAV separation < 50 m, out-of-bounds, no-fly incurs penalties
- LeakageProxy: increases if headings align toward eavesdropper sector with low AN; reduced by higher AN or jammer mode

Episode length ≈ 400 steps or when battery low.

## Baselines
- circle_strategy: both UAVs circle opposite centers; fixed splits 0.5 time / 0.2 AN
- greedy_strategy: comms (move to user centroid, time split=0.2) or sense (maximize baseline, time split=0.8)

## Scripts
- Training: `src/training/train_sac.py`, `src/training/train_td3.py`
- Evaluation: `src/eval/eval_rollout.py`
- Plots: `src/eval/plots.py`
- Pareto sweep: `src/scripts/make_pareto.py`

## Roadmap
- [ ] MAPPO centralized critic (PettingZoo-style wrapper)
- [ ] Rich channel (LoS/NLoS), sensing CRB proxies, RIS
- [ ] Security extensions: cooperative jammer, adaptive AN

## Notes
- Deterministic seeding supported
- Reward terms scaled to target total ~[-1,1]
- Fails fast on NaNs; prints periodic logs

